<task id="021" project="ai-json-prompt-schema-system">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement JSON Schema Draft-07 Generation</title>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api, implement</tags>
    <estimate>3h</estimate>
    <dependencies>001, 020</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Convert output.fields definitions to JSON Schema Draft-07 for Azure OpenAI structured output (constrained decoding).</goal>
    <context>
      When structuredOutput is true, the renderer converts output.fields into a JSON Schema that Azure OpenAI
      uses for constrained decoding — the AI is physically unable to return invalid JSON.
      The JSON Schema includes: type mappings (string→string, number→number), enum values (from $choices or inline),
      array items schema, nested object properties, required fields, and constraints (maxLength, minimum, maximum).
      The generated schema is returned as RenderedPrompt.JsonSchema for use with GetStructuredCompletionAsync.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Generate JSON Schema Draft-07 (compatible with Azure OpenAI response_format)
      - Map all OutputFieldDefinition types: string, number, boolean, array, object
      - Include enum values from $choices resolution and inline enum
      - Include constraints: maxLength, minimum, maximum
      - All output fields are required by default
      - Nested objects and array items must have proper schema
      - Schema must be valid for Azure OpenAI structured output API
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-json-prompt-schema-system/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-json-prompt-schema-system/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read design.md "GENERATE OUTPUT SCHEMA" (Pipeline Step 7) for generation rules</step>
    <step order="2">Research Azure OpenAI JSON Schema requirements for response_format</step>
    <step order="3">Add JsonSchemaGenerator helper to PromptSchemaRenderer or as separate utility:
      - GenerateJsonSchema(fields: OutputFieldDefinition[], resolvedEnums) → JsonObject
      - Type mapping for each field type
      - Enum injection from $choices resolution
      - Array items schema
      - Required properties list</step>
    <step order="4">Integrate into renderer: when structuredOutput=true, set RenderedPrompt.JsonSchema</step>
    <step order="5">Add brief text instruction to prompt: "Return valid JSON matching the provided schema"</step>
    <step order="6">Verify build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Bash(dotnet build)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PromptSchemaRenderer.cs (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Generated JSON Schema is valid Draft-07</criterion>
    <criterion>All field types map correctly (string, number, boolean, array, object)</criterion>
    <criterion>Enum values from $choices appear in JSON Schema</criterion>
    <criterion>Array items and nested objects have proper sub-schemas</criterion>
    <criterion>Schema is compatible with Azure OpenAI response_format</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
